              <tr>
                <td width="186" valign="top" class="row1" nowrap> <span class="largetext"><a name="7008"></a><b>Areilla Elentari</b></span><br>
                  <span class="smalltext">Friend Of The KoA<br>
                  <img src="http://www.southbronx.net/~fubar/knight.gif" alt="Friend Of The KoA" title="Friend Of The KoA" border="0" /><br /><br>
                  <br>
                  Joined: 20 Dec 2002<br>
                  Posts: 12<br>
                  Location: Nexus, Moon</span></td>
                <td valign="top" class="row1"> <span class="smalltext"><b>Very Sad News</b></span>
                  <p><span class="largetext"><span style="font-style: italic"><span style="color: blue"><span style="font-weight: bold">*stares off to the distance daydreaming* 
<br />

<br />
Areilla makes the final rounds and takes the last flag off the wall and
<br />
folds it. Placing it with all of her personal belongings and motioning for
<br />
rocky to take them.
<br />

<br />
She walks over to her chair in the guild hall and stares at the throne with
<br />
tears in her eyes. In the distance she hears the faint voices and laughter
<br />
of all the knights who have come and gone and have at one time called this
<br />
castle home. 
<br />

<br />
"My Queen, it's time" Khadgarr says 
<br />

<br />
She looks up at him with a knowing glance. 
<br />

<br />
"I'll leave you with a few minutes I will be waiting outside with Tritun."
<br />
he says with a tender voice. 
<br />

<br />
Rocky returns to her side after bringing the last of her things outside 
<br />

<br />
She places her hand out before her and a crown appears in her hands. 
<br />

<br />
Areilla closes her eyes and kisses it goodbye and places the crown on the
<br />
throne. 
<br />

<br />
She leaves the guild halls and out to the silent courtyard and thru the
<br />
front gates and up the road to where Khadgarr and Tritun stand. 
<br />

<br />
"We had a blast didn't we?" as she wipes the tears from her eyes. 
<br />

<br />
"Yes we did!" answered Tritun with a sad smile. 
<br />

<br />
With a nod Areilla chants a spell and the castle disappears as she blew a
<br />
kiss in to the air. 
<br />

<br />
The only home she's ever known now gone she turns to her traveling mates and
<br />
says. 
<br />

<br />
"May the new adventures begin" and without turning back they leave the site
<br />
that once held a home to the Knights of Areilla.
<br />
</span></span></span>
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: brown">/ooc
<br />

<br />
Being the stubborn red headed high elf I am, I refused to think of KoA not
<br />
being around but times and people change and it has come to pass that KoA
<br />
will no longer be. Sadly yes, KoA will be closing its doors on Friday at
<br />
Midnight EST in Butcherblock @ the Chess board and I will be disbanding the
<br />
guild. I can no longer run it physically or emotionally. We have had 3 GREAT
<br />
years and have tried to make "our vision" work to no avail. How many times
<br />
can we beat a dead horse? Rather than continue as is, I feel it will be
<br />
better for all in the long run that we disband. Trust me this is not fancy
<br />
fit of furry on my part it's with much thought I have come to this VERY
<br />
difficult decision. I loved this guild and everything it stood for. This is
<br />
very hard for me, this is my home. I am leaving myself homeless as well but
<br />
the fact is we can no longer go on as a guild. This is no one person's fault
<br />
it just happened. For this I am very sorry. We have to move on and try our
<br />
hands at something else.
<br />

<br />

<br />
The board will continue to be here for well however long we can have it but
<br />
it will be here for the next year at least. I will delete a lot of stuff and
<br />
probably only have maybe 2 sections for us to bullshit around in. 
<br />

<br />
In game we will have a chat channel set up for all KoA'ers and friends to
<br />
keep in contact with each other the chat channel is KoA no password. Please
<br />
be sure to join it and keep into touch. I know I will be there and I hope
<br />
you will too. 
<br />

<br />
On Friday at about 10 to midnight I will be in Butcherblock were KoA was
<br />
born and where it will be laid to rest. Khadgarr will transfer leader ship
<br />
back to me and I will disband all members leaving just myself and then I
<br />
will do the final commands to disband the guild. 
<br />

<br />
If you would like to join your fellow knights and say goodbye to our beloved
<br />
guild or give me moral support on this please join me on Friday. I'll
<br />
probably need it.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Once a Knight... Always a Knight at heart & within my heart is where you
<br />
will remain!
<br />

<br />
Amy
<br />

<br />
The real girl behind the Mage
<br />
</span></span> <img src="images/smiles/icon_cry.gif" alt="icon_cry.gif" border="0" />  <img src="images/smiles/icon_cry.gif" alt="icon_cry.gif" border="0" />  <img src="images/smiles/icon_cry.gif" alt="icon_cry.gif" border="0" />  <img src="images/smiles/icon_cry.gif" alt="icon_cry.gif" border="0" />  <img src="images/smiles/icon_cry.gif" alt="icon_cry.gif" border="0" />  <img src="images/smiles/icon_cry.gif" alt="icon_cry.gif" border="0" />  <img src="images/smiles/icon_cry.gif" alt="icon_cry.gif" border="0" />  <img src="images/smiles/icon_cry.gif" alt="icon_cry.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
For those guild members whom want to reply to this please check the members section....<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.brellrants.net/knightsofareilla/index.php" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.southbronx.net/~fubar/WoW/springsig.jpg" border="0"></a>
<br />
KoA & Brell Serilis will live in my heart forever!</span><span class="smalltext"></span></p>
                </td>
              </tr>
